    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style and culture of one of the six subgroups of Lakota who had separated from each other by the early 19th century. Today the Oglala reside primarily in the Pine Ridge Indian Reservation in South Dakota bordering Nebraska.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
